properties.pdsode:Description: "This data product is a global olivine spectral parameter map of Mars at a resolution of 40 ppd (about 1.5 km at the equator). It is based on reflectance data acquired by the Mars Express OMEGA hyperspectral camera from January 2004 to August 2010. The OMEGA Flight Experiment Data Records (EDR) are the source for this data product. It corresponds to the map that was produced and published by Ody et al. ([ODY_JGR2012], figure 9a). This map, in simple cylindrical projection, is in the form of an image where each sample represents the highest value of the olive spectral parameter values calculated within a 0.025 by 0.025 degree area. Olivine has a broad, complex absorption centered near 1 micrometer that varies in width, position, and shape with grain size and Fo number. This olivine spectral parameter (OSP2) is sensitive to olivine with high iron content and/or large grain size and/or high abundance. For more information on how this map was produced and how it can be best interpreted, please refer to the original publication available in the DOCUMENT directory of this data set."
